                </div>


                <p>The all-new Seltos ensures that its bold looks are backed by impressive performance, offering a versatile range of engine and transmission options to suit every driving style. This commitment to delivering a fun and engaging driving experience is a core reason for the Seltos's popularity.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700"> The Trio of Powerful Engines</span></p>
                <p>The Seltos is offered with a choice of three BS6 Phase 2 compliant engines, each delivering a blend of power and efficiency:</p>
                <ol start="1">
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Smartstream G1.5 T-GDi Petrol Engine: </span>This is the flagship powerhouse, a new-generation turbocharged engine. It delivers a thrilling <span class="font-weight-700"> 160 PS (approx. 158 bhp) </span>of power and a robust peak torque of<span class="font-weight-700">  253 Nm@1,500–3,500 rpm. </span>It is paired with either a 6-speed Intelligent Manual Transmission (iMT) or a quick-shifting<span class="font-weight-700"> 7-speed Dual Clutch Transmission (DCT),</span> promising spirited performance for highway runs.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Smartstream G1.5 Naturally Aspirated (NA) Petrol Engine:</span> The refined NA petrol engine is perfect for city commutes, producing a smooth <span class="font-weight-700"> 115 PS (approx. 113 bhp) </span>of power and <span class="font-weight-700"> 144 Nm</span> of torque. Transmission options include a 6-speed Manual or a <span class="font-weight-700"> Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT), </span>known as Intelligent Variable Transmission (iVT) by Kia.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> 1.5l CRDi VGT Diesel Engine: </span>The ever-reliable diesel motor generates <span class="font-weight-700"> 116 PS (approx. 114 bhp)</span> of power and a strong<span class="font-weight-700">  250 Nm of torque,</span> providing excellent drivability across the rev range. Buyers can choose between a 6-speed Manual or a smooth <span class="font-weight-700"> 6-speed Torque Converter Automatic (AT).</span></li>
                </ol>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700"> Transmission and Efficiency</span></p>
                <p>The availability of six distinct powertrain combinations ensures that there is a Seltos for everyone, from the budget-conscious commuter to the performance enthusiast. The 7-speed DCT and 6-speed AT automatic variants also benefit from features like <span class="font-weight-700"> Paddle Shifters</span> for manual gear control and multiple<span class="font-weight-700">  Drive Mode Select options (Eco/Normal/Sport),</span> along with specialized <span class="font-weight-700"> Traction Control Modes (Sand/Mud/Snow) </span>to enhance control in challenging conditions.</p>
