                <p><span class="font-weight-700"> Standard and Passive Safety</span></p>
                <p>Kia now offers <span class="font-weight-700"> six airbags as standard</span> across all variants of the Seltos, ensuring maximum occupant protection regardless of the trim level. This commitment to safety is backed by a comprehensive suite of passive safety features that are standard even on the base model:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> All-Wheel Disc Brakes</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) and Brake Assist System (BAS)</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and Vehicle Stability Management (VSM)</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Hill-start Assist Control (HAC)</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Highline Tyre Pressure Monitoring System (TPMS)</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> ISOFIX Child Seat Anchorages</span></li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700"> ADAS Level 2: Advanced Driver Assistance System</span></p>
                <p>The most significant safety upgrade is the integration of<span class="font-weight-700">  Level 2 Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS)</span> in the top variants (HTX (A) and GTX (A)/X-Line (A)). This advanced suite utilizes a combination of cameras and radars to offer semi-autonomous driving capabilities, thereby enhancing driver vigilance and overall road safety.</p>
                <p>The ADAS Level 2 suite includes up to 21 autonomous features, such as:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Forward Collision Warning (FCW)</span> and <span class="font-weight-700"> Forward Collision-Avoidance Assist (FCA) </span>(covering car, pedestrian, cyclist, and junction turning).</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Lane Departure Warning (LDW), Lane Keeping Assist (LKA), and Lane Following Assist (LFA)</span>.
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Smart Cruise Control (SCC) with Stop & Go </span>functionality, which manages speed and distance from the vehicle ahead, even in stop-and-go traffic.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Blind Spot Collision Warning (BCW)and Blind Spot Collision Avoidance Assist (BCA). </span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> Rear Cross Traffic Collision Warning (RCCW) and Avoidance Assist (RCCA). </span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> High Beam Assist (HBA) </span> and <span class="font-weight-700"> Driver Attention Warning (DAW). </span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700"> 360-Degree Camera  </span>with <span class="font-weight-700"> Blind View Monitor (BVM) </span>projected onto the digital cluster for unparalleled parking and maneuvering visibility.</li>
                </ul>

