                <p>The Kia Seltos is strategically divided into three key lines—Tech Line, GT Line, and X Line—each offering a distinct personality and feature set. Understanding the variants is key to choosing the right vehicle.</p>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Tech Line (HTE, HTK, HTX)</span></p>
                <p>The Tech Line forms the core of the Seltos offering, balancing value and functionality.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">HTE & HTE (O): </span>The entry points are surprisingly well-equipped, now featuring <span class="font-weight-700">6 airbags, ESC, All-Wheel Disc Brakes,</span> and a <span class="font-weight-700">10.25-inch HD Touchscreen with Wireless Smartphone Connectivity</span> as standard. The HTE(O) adds practical features like a 60:40 split rear seat and three adjustable rear headrests.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">HTK & HTK (O): </span>These variants introduce significant convenience features, including <span class="font-weight-700">Smart Key with Push Button Start/Stop, Auto-Folding ORVMs, Rear Wiper and Defogger,</span> and stylish 17-inch alloy wheels. The HTK(O) further sweetens the deal with a<span class="font-weight-700"> Panoramic Sunroof and Wireless Phone Charger.</span></li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">HTX & HTX (A): </span>The HTX is the luxury sweet spot, boasting the <span class="font-weight-700">12.3-inch Touchscreen, Bose 8-speaker system, Dual-Zone Auto AC, and Front Ventilated Seats. </span>The HTX(A) is the first variant to introduce a partial Level 2 ADAS suite, making advanced safety accessible.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">GT Line and X-Line (GTX, X-Line)</span></p>
                <p>These lines are aimed at the enthusiast who desires top-tier features, performance, and aggressive styling.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">GTX & GTX (A): </span>The GTX line is visually sporty, featuring dark chrome accents, gloss black cladding,<span class="font-weight-700"> 18-inch machined alloy wheels,</span> and sportier interiors. The highlight is the powerful 1.5L Turbo Petrol DCT engine option. The GTX(A) adds the full Level 2 ADAS suite, the 360-Degree Camera, and the full digital cluster.</li>
